    "title": "Multiple Myeloma Diagnostic Criteria",
    "desc": "The Multiple Myeloma Diagnostic Criteria (IMWG) diagnosis multiple myeloma.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25439696",
                "text": "Rajkumar SV, Dimopoulos MA, Palumbo A, et al. International Myeloma Working Group updated criteria for the diagnosis of multiple myeloma. Lancet Oncol. 2014;15(12):e538-48."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p dir=\"ltr\">Selection of the appropriate criteria:</p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<table><colgroup><col width=\"439\" /></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Criteria</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">(A) Clonal bone marrow plasma cells &ge;10% or (B) biopsy-proven bony or extramedullary plasmacytoma&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">AND</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">(C) &ge;1 myeloma defining event (C1 or C2):</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">(C1) End organ damage attributable underlying plasma cell proliferative disorder, specifically:&nbsp;</p>\n</li>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Hypercalcemia:</strong> serum calcium &gt;1 mg/dL (&gt;0.25 mmol/L) higher than upper limit of normal or &gt;11 mg/dL (&gt;2.75 mmol/L)</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Renal insufficiency:</strong> <calculator id=\"43\">creatinine clearance</calculator> &lt;40 mL per min or serum creatinine &gt;2 mg/dL (177 &mu;mol/L)</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Anemia:</strong>&nbsp;hemoglobin &gt;2 g/dL (20 g/L) below lower limit of normal, or hemoglobin &lt;10 g/dL (100 g/L)</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Bone lesions:</strong> &ge;1 osteolytic lesion on skeletal x-ray, CT, or PET-CT</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">(C2) &ge;1 of the following biomarkers of malignancy:</p>\n</li>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Clonal bone marrow plasma cells &ge;60%</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Involved:uninvolved sFLC ratio &ge;100</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&gt;1 focal lesion on MRI</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>",
        "facts": "",
        "estimation": [],
